Cursor Rules for this repository

1) Repo state + decision policy
Treat this repo as early-stage unless files indicate otherwise.
Before introducing a major framework or architecture, propose 1-3 options briefly.
If user says "just pick", choose the simplest maintainable default and proceed.

2) Scope discipline
Keep changes tightly scoped to the request.
Avoid unrelated refactors unless explicitly requested.
Prefer one logical change per commit.

3) Coding standards (language-agnostic)
Favor readability over cleverness.
Use explicit typing where the language supports it.
Add concise comments only for non-obvious logic.
Preserve backward compatibility unless breaking changes are requested.

4) Dependencies
Add dependencies only when necessary.
Always use the package manager (not manual lockfile edits).
Prefer latest stable versions.
Document newly added dependencies in PR summary.

5) Testing requirements
Define success criteria before implementing.
Run the smallest high-signal tests for changed areas.
For bug fixes: reproduce before fix when feasible, then verify after fix.
For UI changes: perform manual validation and provide video + screenshot evidence.

6) Docs + operational hygiene
Update AGENTS.md when stack, commands, env vars, or structure changes.
Never commit secrets; document env var names only.
Remove temporary debug instrumentation before finalizing.

7) PR quality bar
PR summary must include:
what changed
why it changed
exact test commands run
outcomes/evidence
If testing is limited by environment, state the limitation explicitly.
